postCaption: Troughback: Art & Coffee, Capsule & Design. text: :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes::smiling_face_with_heart-eyes::face_savoring_food::face_savoring_food::brown_heart::brown_heart::hot_beverage::hot_beverage::white_heart::white_heart::star-struck::star-struck:
postCaption: Iced Cinnamon Dolce Latte I knew not to froth my cold foam in the tiny espresso shot glass anyways! What I used - 2 starbucks blonde espresso pods - 1 - 2 tsps of Cinnamon Dolce syrup (Jordan’s skinny syrups) - creamer - heavy whipping cream - ice Cold Foam: - 1/3 cup of heavy cream - 1-2 tbsp creamer or milk - 1/2 tsp cinnamon dolce syrup Recipe 1. Brew your espresso shots and add both your syrup and espresso to your drinking glass. Mix together well. 2. Next, add your ice and then milk (or creamer) to your coffee. Add your milk/creamer if preferred. 3. Froth your heavy cream, creamer or milk, and syrup until you have a thick consistency. 4. Add frothed milk to your drinking glass and enjoy! • • • • • • • • • • • • • • • #thecoffeegirly #pinterest #pinterestinspired #coffee #coffeelover #coffeeaddict #coffeegram #coffeebar #nespressovertuo #icedcoffee #icedcoffeelovers #morning #morningroutine #morningcoffee #vlog #dailyvlog #icedcoffeelovers #nespresso #vertuonext #icedcoffeerecipes #coffeeaesthetic

text: Happy gotcha day sweet Pearl! :two_hearts::smiling_cat_with_heart-eyes::sparkling_heart:
postCaption: :paw_prints: IT'S MY GOTCHA DAY! :paw_prints: Today is a special day - it's the day I found my furever home :yellow_heart: One year ago, my dad raced 2hrs north to Morriset to pick me up. Another lockdown was due to start at midnight that day, which meant my pawrents had to make the decision to pick me up earlier than expected. I was 6 months old at the time. According to my breeder, my original owner had fallen through when I was younger. Then, my breeder decided to keep me so I could find fame and glory as a show cat but due to covid - there were no shows! So my breeder made the difficult decision to give me up. And here I am! I'm heavily loved on by my mum and dad. I chase ribbons all day, steal pen lids, eat books and feature in my mum's work reviews! I spent the morning snuggling in bed with meowmy before knocking every object off her side table until she decided to get up :smiling_face_with_hearts: She wouldn't change anything for the world though! #ragdoll #ragdollkitten #ragdollcat #ragdollsofinstagram #catsofinstagram #catlover #instacats #petsofinstagram #catsofaustralia #catworld #catstagram #dailyfluff #pet_delight #kittensofinstagram #petoftheday #catoftheday #catsdaily #catsoftheworld #misspearlyroo #meowsofaustralia #hillspetau #featured_whiskers #meowfeature #meowstagram #hoomanswithcats #cutestpetsofaustralia #lavazzacoffeemachine #lavazzadesea #lavazzaaustralia

text: Just 2 considerations... the light flashes quickly after 5 coffees to indicate that the drawer is full of capsules (the pods are the paper ones)..2, more importantly, when the machine is not in use the lever must remain raised until the soft stroke of the lever forward ends and must never ever be closed completely as the coffee perfusion seal gaskets will be ruined with leaks underneath... anyway thanks for the content...:thumbs_up:

text: I bought the lavazza a modo mio joilie, a few days ago. The coffee is excellent. It is not strong and is close to that of the bar. However, trying the various blends included in the free box of capsules I noticed a certain acidity/reflux after 30 minutes. Never had this problem with the moka using the same lavazza blends. I would be curious to know if in addition to the ground coffee they also put oils or preservatives in the capsule, such as to create this sense of acidity

text: My thoughts on this device are very negative. The expectations listed in the video are much higher than those that you can actually have regarding this coffee machine. Because there is no doubt that many of the functions that you require are not present. Just a few: there is no option to choose between long or short coffee via voice commands. There is no queue of capsules that you can use without having to insert one manually each time. That's why I repeat: the basic functions required by a coffee machine with Alexa integrated are not present in this product.

text: Hi Claudio, the only comment that comes to mind watching the video is that it is a "monstrous" machine, but in a somewhat negative sense of the term: I, who am not at all inclined towards technology, would feel truly embarrassed even just getting close to a "phenomenon" of this kind, and then thinking about trying to set up all its programs would make me lose the desire to have a coffee. Who could be the target of such a product? I don't think people of a certain age but probably only young "millennials" who are up to speed with technology, even if perhaps a young person wouldn't want to, or maybe couldn't, spend such a large sum to buy it. I will definitely keep away from it anyway. Of course, great video as always.

text: good afternoon dear Claudio, I really like this machine like a punch in the teeth... no offense but in my opinion it would be good for NASA, at least they are all technological, if I have to have a coffee I like to use a machine like the ones you have, the frog type... this type of machine and for what it costs can make cobwebs.. If I have to spend and then I go for a semi-professional machine that is used manually and you have an excellent coffee, I really don't like this one, maybe because I have an old and closed brain and I don't get along with technology.. I hope I haven't offended you with my point of view on this spaceship, you are a very dear friend and I don't want to lose you because of my big mouth... the only machines I prefer are yours and your coffees, the rest can be hidden... Bye dear Claudio... have a good weekend...

text: Owner of a Lavazza tiny machine I can't help but comment on this video :) beautiful there's no doubt about it, but it has some important shortcomings and for these reasons, in addition to how much it costs, I would NEVER buy it. First of all it doesn't have an internal capsule dispenser and therefore Alexa doesn't make sense in my opinion; if I have to go there anyway to put the capsule how much is it worth that I push a button and make coffee, just how could they make it the first "super automatic" machine; it would have been perfect, even at €100 more if they had made Alexa useful for turning on the machine, choosing the type of capsule, choosing whether to add sugar and any quantity, choosing whether to make a short coffee, espresso, long, turning off the machine. And maybe over time offer updates on the possible temperature etc etc. Look how many they would have sold and even at €500 I would have bought it. In any case I take this opportunity to always thank Claudio for his videos and his channel.
